Name:          Florence Nightingale
Lived:         1820 - 1910
Nationality:   English
Field:         Medicine
Known For:     Modern nursing
Contribution:  Founded modern nursing; used statistics; reduced Crimean War mortality 40% to 2%
Quote:         "I attribute my success to this: I never gave or took any excuse."

Name:          Leonardo da Vinci
Lived:         1452 - 1519
Nationality:   Italian
Field:         Art/Science
Known For:     Mona Lisa, anatomy
Contribution:  Renaissance polymath; Mona Lisa; anatomical drawings; flying machine designs
Quote:         "Learning never exhausts the mind."

Name:          Ada Lovelace
Lived:         1815 - 1852
Nationality:   English
Field:         Computing
Known For:     First computer algorithm
Contribution:  Wrote first algorithm for Babbage's machine; recognized computing potential
Quote:         "The Analytical Engine weaves algebraic patterns."

